title: Minna Hesso
content:
Minna Hesso (born 15 March 1976) is a Finnish snowboarder. 

She was born in Vantaa. She competed at the 1998 Winter Olympics, in halfpipe, and also at the  2002 Winter Olympics.[1]

Hesso moved to Verbier, Switzerland, in her early twenties.[2]
